│                                                                                                                      │
│  Agent: Executive Intelligence Analyst for AMD                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                      │
│  Final Answer:                                                                                                       │
│  - **Dr. Lisa Su — Chair, President & CEO**                                                                          │
│    **Tenure:** CEO since Oct. 2014; board member since 2014; president/chair roles added subsequently.               │
│    **Background:** Electrical engineer and longtime semiconductor executive. Joined AMD in 2012, previously served   │
│  as COO and SVP/GM of Global Business Units. Prior roles include senior leadership at **Freescale Semiconductor**,   │
│  **IBM**, and **Texas Instruments**. Widely credited with leading AMD’s turnaround and repositioning around          │
│  high-performance computing, data center, and AI.                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                      │
│  - **Jean Hu — EVP, CFO & Treasurer**                                                                                │
│    **Tenure:** CFO since Jan. 2023.                                                                                  │
│    **Background:** Finance executive with public-company semiconductor and industrial experience. Previously CFO at  │
│  **Marvell Technology** and before that held senior finance roles at **Qorvo** and **International Paper**. At AMD,  │
│  she leads financial planning, capital allocation, accounting, tax, treasury, and investor-facing finance            │
│  functions.                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                      │
│  - **Mark Papermaster — EVP & CTO**                                                                                  │
│    **Tenure:** CTO since 2011.                                                                                       │
│    **Background:** Veteran engineer and product-development leader. Before AMD, he held senior engineering roles at  │
│  **Cisco** and **IBM**, and was also known for a senior hardware engineering stint at **Apple**. At AMD he oversees  │
│  corporate technical direction plus core engineering and product-development execution.                              │
│                                                                                                                      │
│  - **Darren Grasby — EVP, Chief Sales Officer & President, EMEA**                                                    │
│    **Tenure:** On AMD’s executive leadership team for several years; current CSO title listed on AMD leadership      │
│  page.                                                                                                               │
│    **Background:** Career sales and go-to-market executive with deep semiconductor/channel experience. Leads global  │
│  sales and customer engagement, important as AMD scales data center and AI deployments.                              │
│                                                                                                                      │
│  - **Forrest Norrod — EVP & GM, Data Center Solutions Business Unit**                                                │
│    **Tenure:** Senior AMD executive since 2018.                                                                      │
│    **Background:** Former **Dell EMC** executive with strong enterprise infrastructure credentials. Runs one of      │
│  AMD’s most strategic businesses: server CPUs, accelerators, and data-center platform execution.                     │
│                                                                                                                      │
│  **Leadership assessment (≈170 words):**                                                                             │
│  AMD’s C-suite looks **strong**. The core leadership triangle—Lisa Su, Mark Papermaster, and now Jean Hu—combines    │
│  deep technical credibility with proven operating and capital-markets discipline. Stability is a clear positive: Su  │
│  has led AMD for more than a decade, and Papermaster has been CTO since 2011, giving the company unusual continuity  │
│  for long-cycle semiconductor roadmaps. That matters because AMD’s gains in CPUs, data center, and AI have depended  │
│  on consistent architectural execution rather than short-term restructuring. Hu is newer, but her prior CFO          │
│  experience at Marvell adds relevant semiconductor finance depth and supports credibility with investors. Beyond     │
│  the formal C-suite, leaders like Darren Grasby and Forrest Norrod strengthen commercial and enterprise execution,   │
│  especially in hyperscale and server markets. Overall, this is a seasoned, high-functioning team with strong domain  │
│  expertise and evidence of execution against ambitious product roadmaps. Main watchpoint: continued scaling in AI    │
│  against larger rivals will test bench depth and operating complexity. Still, leadership quality appears well above  │
│  average for the sector.                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                      │
│  **Overall rating: Strong**                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                      │
